solutions.content:
SortedSet is actually BST.
It has a method 'GetViewBetween(lower, upper)', what can be used to check if we have already had an element in range 't'.
So all we need is to run through the array once, adding new values to the BST and removing the least 'k' value from it.
When ve find any item in 'ViewBetween' -- that means we found Duplicate.

```
    public bool ContainsNearbyAlmostDuplicate(int[] nums, int k, int t) {
        if (nums == null || nums.Length == 0 || k < 1 || t < 0) return false;

        var sortedSet = new SortedSet<int>();

        for (var i = 0; i < nums.Length; i++) {
            if (ContainsElementsInRange(sortedSet, nums[i], t)) return true;

            if (sortedSet.Count == k) sortedSet.Remove(nums[i - k]);
            if (!sortedSet.Add(nums[i])) return true;
        }
        return false;
    }

    private static bool ContainsElementsInRange(SortedSet<int> sortedSet, int center, int radius) {

        var lower = (long) center - radius < int.MinValue ? int.MinValue : center - radius;
        var upper = (long) center + radius > int.MaxValue ? int.MaxValue : center + radius;

        return sortedSet.GetViewBetween(lower, upper).Count > 0;
    }
```

And here is another solution using Dictionary of buckets instead of BST.
I've outspokenly stolen buckets idea from [here](https://leetcode.com/problems/contains-duplicate-iii/discuss/61645/AC-O(N)-solution-in-Java-using-buckets-with-explanation) ).

```
    public bool ContainsNearbyAlmostDuplicate(int[] nums, int k, int t) {
        if (k < 1 || t < 0) return false;
        var map = new Dictionary<long, long>();

        for (var i = 0; i < nums.Length; i++) {
            var (key, value) = GetBucket(nums[i], t);
            if (!map.TryAdd(key, value)
                || map.ContainsKey(key - 1) && value - map[key - 1] <= t
                || map.ContainsKey(key + 1) && map[key + 1] - value <= t) return true;
            if (map.Count > k) map.Remove(GetBucket(nums[i - k], t).Key);
        }
        return false;
    }

    private static KeyValuePair<long, long> GetBucket(int num, int t) {
        var value = (long) num - int.MinValue;
        var key = value / ((long) t + 1);
        return new KeyValuePair<long, long>(key, value);
    }
