solutions.content:
A sliding window of size `t+1` is used so that we don't have to handle the case when `t=0`. Since Python 3.7, dictionaries are ordered, so we can implement LRU cache functionality using `buckets.pop(next(iter(buckets)))`.

```python
def containsNearbyAlmostDuplicate(self, nums: List[int], k: int, t: int) -> bool:
	buckets = {}
	for i, num in enumerate(nums):
		v = num // (t + 1)
		for bucket in range(v - 1, v + 2):
			if bucket in buckets and abs(buckets[bucket] - num) <= t: return True
		buckets[v] = num
		if(len(buckets) > k): buckets.pop(next(iter(buckets)))
	return False
```

