We will use treeset as a data structure because we need to find out the minimum and maximum in the structure, more precisely INFINIMUM and SUPREMUM of that number, that is, the highest minimum close to this number and the smaller one that is in the data set(infinimum)  and   the smallest maximum higher than that number located in the data set(supremum). Infinimum is located with the floor api(), and will be done the operation nums[i] - treeSet.floor((long)nums[i]) <= t that satisfies the condition. Analogous to supremum, it will be  with ceil api and will be done the operation treeSet.ceiling(((long)nums[i]) - nums[i] <= t to check the condition.  The size of the data structure must be maximum k and if it is exceeded we will remove the oldest element located at the i-k position in the nums array.


