`lb` is the iterator to lower_bound of `target`, i.e., the smallest possible value such that `lb` >= `target`

`lb == end(nums) || *lb != target` indicates `target` is not found

`lb-begin(nums)` is the position of `target` if found

```
class Solution {
public:
    int search(vector<int>& nums, int target) {
        auto lb = lower_bound(begin(nums), end(nums), target);
        return ((lb == end(nums) || *lb != target) ? -1 : (lb-begin(nums)));
    }
};
```

Time complexity : `O(log n)`

