Binary Search Using Recursive Approach in Java

# Approach
Firstly, we create two non static global variables 'int[] arr' and 'int key'

In the main function we initialise the global variables to the parameters from the 'int search' function such that we don't have to pass them again and again while calling binarySearch function

Copy input parameter's 'int[] nums' array elements to the global variable 'static int arr[]' and likewise we assign global variable 'key' to input 'target'

We recursively call function 'binary_search()' having low and high as the parameters (initially 0 , length of array -1 )

We return the value of this funciton.

- Space complexity:
    O(log N)

# Code
```
class Solution {

    //global variables

    int[] arr; 
    int key;

    int search(int[] nums, int target) 
    {
        arr = nums //copying nums to global variable arr
        key = target; //copying target to global variable key
        return (binary_search(0,arr.length - 1));
    }

    int binary_search(int low, int high)
    {
        int mid = low + (high - low) / 2;

        if(arr[mid] == key)
            return mid;

        if(low == high)
            return -1;

        if(arr[mid] < key)
            return binary_search(mid+1 , high);

        return binary_search(0,mid);
    }

}
```

