solutions.content:
we use `(high+low)/2` lead to an error if high is `Integer.MAX_VALUE()`.  but if we use `(high-low)/2 + low` which avoid overflow error.

## Java Solution
```java
class Solution {

	// iterative
    public int search(int[] nums, int target) {

		// Corner case
        if(nums == null || nums.length == 0) return -1;

        int low = 0;
        int high = nums.length-1;

        while(low <= high){
            int mid = (high-low)/2 + low;
            if(nums[mid] == target) return mid;
            if(nums[mid] < target) low = mid + 1;
            else high = mid  - 1;
	    }
        return -1;
    }

	// Recursive 
	public static int Rsearch(int[] nums, int low, int high, int target){

		if(low > high) return -1;

		int mid = low + (high-low)/2;
		if(target == nums[mid])
			return mid;
		else if(target < nums[mid])
			return Rsearch(nums, low, mid-1, target);
		else
			return Rsearch(nums, mid+1, high, target);
	}
}
```
